1. When processing boundary rows (scanline >= image_height), `y[i]` points to `empty.get()` which is only `cinfo->image_width` bytes
2. But when `need_padding` is true, the code does `memcpy(y_intrm[i], y[i], cinfo->image_width)` which is fine
