Actually, wait - let me re-read this. The issue is more subtle. When `jpeg_write_raw_data()` is called with grayscale (1 component), it still processes MCU blocks. For grayscale with 2x2 sampling factors, an MCU is 8x8 pixels. So 16 scanlines would be 2 MCU rows.

The bug is that the check `if (processed != kCompressBatchSize / 2)` expects 8 rows back but gets 16. This causes the function to return `false`, which is an error condition but not a crash.

